#: ../../B/brain-damaged.rst:5
msgid "brain-damaged"
msgstr "brain-damaged"

#: ../../B/brain-damaged.rst:7
msgid "adj\\."
msgstr "形容詞"

#: ../../B/brain-damaged.rst:10
msgid ""
"[common; generalization of \"Honeywell Brain Damage\" (HBD), a theoretical "
"disease invented to explain certain utter cretinisms in Honeywell "
":ref:`Multics`\\] adj. Obviously wrong; :ref:`cretinous`\\; "
":ref:`demented`\\. There is an implication that the person responsible must "
"have suffered brain damage, because he should have known better. Calling "
"something brain-damaged is really bad; it also implies it is unusable, and "
"that its failure to work is due to poor design rather than some accident. "
"\"Only six monocase characters per file name? Now that's brain-damaged!\""
msgstr ""
"[一般的。Honeywell\\ :ref:`Multics`\\ における特定のまったくの愚行を説明するために考案された理論上の病「Honeywell"
" Brain Damage」(HBD)の一般化]形容詞。明らかに間違っている、\\ :ref:`cretinous`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`demented`\\ "
"。責任者は脳に損傷を受けていたに違いない、もっとよく分かっていてしかるべきだったのだから、という含みがある。何かをbrain-"
"damagedと呼ぶのは本当にひどい。それが使い物にならないこと、そしてその動作不良が何らかの事故ではなくまずい設計によるものであることも含意する。「ファイル名につき大文字だけ6文字?"
" さあ、それこそbrain-damagedだ!」"

#: ../../B/brain-damaged.rst:18
msgid ""
"[esp. in the Mac world] May refer to free demonstration software that has "
"been deliberately crippled in some way so as not to compete with the product"
" it is intended to sell. Syn. :ref:`crippleware`\\."
msgstr ""
"[特にMacの世界]売り込もうとする製品と競合しないように意図的に何らかの形で機能制限された、無料のデモソフトウェアを指すことがある。\\ "
":ref:`crippleware`\\ の同義語。"
